pageContext.claim: “When they charge 40 percent tariffs on our cars going into China, and we charge them nothing coming into our country. When they raise their tariff from 10 percent to 25 percent and then to 40 percent.”
pageContext.analysis: China in 2018 lowered its tariff on car imports to 15 percent. They threatened but did not follow through with an additional 25 percent tariff (40 percent total). That was in response to Trump's tariffs.
